This paper proposes a novel approach to approximate aggregation on big data, which is a common problem in database systems and data science. The paper focuses on leveraging individual differences of samples from a statistical perspective, which is related to data management and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DB (database), cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), and cs.LG (machine learning). Additionally, the paper also involves iterative improvement and constraint relations, which are related to optimization and information theory, leading to cs.AI (artificial intelligence) and cs.IT (information theory) as possible sub-categories.
